description.narrative: Community health workers trained in the priority regions provided ORS/zinc treatment to 14%, 14%, 20% and 8% children with diarrhea in Far-North, North, Adamawa and East regions respectively. They also paid postpartum home visits to newborns within the first week of life to 13% (Far-North), 14% (North), 16% (Adamawa) and 10% (East). Promotion of Kangaroo care continued at institutional level in the East region. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:30/06/2020
